117
00:08:02,700 --> 00:08:04,870
Even the chickens are exhausted!

118
00:08:05,380 --> 00:08:08,070
You don't have the servers anymore, do you?

119
00:08:08,070 --> 00:08:09,940
How did you do it?

120
00:08:09,940 --> 00:08:12,670
I moved all the data to the cloud.

121
00:08:12,670 --> 00:08:15,170
It's cloud computing, Zhou Rui.

122
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:19,190
This is still not what I wanted to say.

123
00:08:20,390 --> 00:08:21,800
Then... Then... Then what do you want to say?

124
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:24,590
No! You taught me this.

125
00:08:25,130 --> 00:08:28,460
To benefit others, they have to need you.

126
00:08:28,460 --> 00:08:30,310
Have you forgotten?

127
00:08:31,850 --> 00:08:37,790
Old Cao, this doesn't sound like something you'd say.

128
00:08:41,690 --> 00:08:45,130
How is it? How does it feel to be needed by others?

129
00:08:45,130 --> 00:08:47,160
Does it feel amazing?

130
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:48,960
How do I say this?

131
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:52,190
It really feels more amazing than making money.

132
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:58,710
Old Cao,

133
00:08:59,770 --> 00:09:02,350
