153
00:10:16,470 --> 00:10:19,780
First, it's to apologize, and then, it's to explain.

154
00:10:21,550 --> 00:10:24,830
Then can I say a few words first?

155
00:10:25,490 --> 00:10:26,850
Alright.

156
00:10:26,850 --> 00:10:30,360
To a business, what is the reason to find customers?

157
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:32,650
What is the standard when choosing a collaboration partner?

158
00:10:32,650 --> 00:10:36,960
Ultimately, what's the most important is probably still the quantity of customer flow.

159
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:39,290
The flow that you mentioned, our management calls it consumer flow.

160
00:10:39,290 --> 00:10:42,340
It isn't a frigid concept, but a living person.

161
00:10:42,340 --> 00:10:45,250
It's you, it's me, and it's them.

162
00:10:45,250 --> 00:10:48,410
Do you really think these people care about your "free of charge?"

163
00:10:48,410 --> 00:10:51,610
- Can you let me finish talking first?
- Director Zhou, please listen to me first.

164
00:10:51,610 --> 00:10:53,740
- But once I finish talking, you can understand what I mean—
- No, no. It's like this.

165
00:10:53,740 --> 00:10:55,530
It's like this!

166
00:10:56,580 --> 00:10:58,560
Listen to me first!

167
00:10:59,630 --> 00:11:01,430
Okay, please.

168
00:11:01,430 --> 00:11:05,950
Your scale is only ten percent of the cardinal number, but it can't satisfy me.

169
00:11:05,950 --> 00:11:08,060
Yes. Your solution may be very cheap, but sorry!

170
00:11:08,060 --> 00:11:11,250
My affiliated group has over a dozen people who work hard every year to earn money.

171
00:11:11,250 --> 00:11:13,200
Each year will burn two million.

172
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:15,900
Sometimes, they burn tens of millions just to hear a sound.

173
00:11:15,900 --> 00:11:19,120
- If we don't have direct profit; of course, I have to withdraw.
- Okay, I'll admit it to you.

174
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:20,790
Free of charge is indeed a gimmick.

175
00:11:20,790 --> 00:11:24,530
In the future, you still have to pay for our operating cost, maintenance fee, and service charge.

176
00:11:24,530 --> 00:11:26,450
It is indeed a huge cost, but do you know?

177
00:11:26,450 --> 00:11:28,520
What I'm doing now is the real direction of the future.

178
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:31,470
You have to be patient to see that I'll be able to gradually incubate it.

179
00:11:31,470 --> 00:11:34,960
First of all, I can't wait for you, and secondly, what you call "cost" isn't a cost.

180
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:37,390
- Time is the real cost.
- Time is...

181
00:11:37,390 --> 00:11:39,830
Sorry, Director Zhou! Can you lower your voices over here?

182
00:11:39,830 --> 00:11:42,380
- We still have other customers here.
- Sorry, sorry!

183
00:11:42,380 --> 00:11:44,080
Thank you, Director Zhou.

184
00:11:52,040 --> 00:11:56,940
President Guo, first of all, I wish you a happy collaboration with Director Luo.

185
00:11:56,940 --> 00:11:59,790
However, I firmly believe that you'll come back to find me.

186
00:11:59,790 --> 00:12:03,730
Because, to me, you all are a bunch of fat rabbits.

187
00:12:06,140 --> 00:12:09,630
[Jieke Company]

188
00:12:16,270 --> 00:12:19,220
What is this? An appeal before sentencing?

189
00:12:19,220 --> 00:12:22,800
- No, this is sales performance.
- Sales performance?

190
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:26,330
Can this be given to the finance department to book into the account?

191
00:12:26,330 --> 00:12:31,810
Or, maybe you can tell me whose name we put on the invoice for your sales performance?

192
00:12:32,370 --> 00:12:36,450
Master, I remember when I first entered this field,

193
00:12:36,450 --> 00:12:39,500
someone once told me something.

194
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:43,620
He said, "For our internet industry, C-end
(TN: C-end is business-to-consumer business model.)"

195
00:12:43,620 --> 00:12:47,580
"and only C-end is the real future."
(TN: C-end = A model where products/services are delivered directly to the end user.)

196
00:12:49,340 --> 00:12:52,270
That person told me that before, too.

197
00:12:53,050 --> 00:12:55,980
After all these years, this is the first time

198
00:12:55,980 --> 00:12:58,230
that you've quoted his words.

199
00:12:58,230 --> 00:12:59,990
This has nothing to do with personal feelings,

200
00:12:59,990 --> 00:13:02,940
but I've been feeling more and more these past few years that

201
00:13:02,940 --> 00:13:05,480
- he makes sense.
- It makes sense technically.

202
00:13:06,730 --> 00:13:10,080
In our internet field, technology and sales can't be separated.

203
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:12,300
Master, you taught me this.

204
00:13:12,300 --> 00:13:15,950
How much of the cash flow can your C-end clients maintain every month?

205
00:13:15,950 --> 00:13:19,800
How much does it cost the company every month for your C-end clients?

206
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:23,160
I've included the project estimate and the expected revenue for the next five years.

207
00:13:23,160 --> 00:13:26,230
You can call the marketing and finance departments over to discuss it.

208
00:13:26,230 --> 00:13:29,860
I thought you wanted to shirk responsibility and didn't want to shoulder it.

209
00:13:29,860 --> 00:13:32,210
It appears you aren't like that.

210
00:13:34,340 --> 00:13:36,470
You're insane.

211
00:13:40,680 --> 00:13:43,430
- Master, why don't you look at it first before we discuss?
- There's no need to look at it.

212
00:13:43,430 --> 00:13:44,900
I'll ask you two questions.

213
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:47,660
First of all, among your customer resources,

214
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:50,040
how many are B-end (business-to-business model), and how many are C-end?

215
00:13:50,040 --> 00:13:51,850
I only have B-end, no C-end.

216
00:13:51,850 --> 00:13:54,120
Second question.

217
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:58,530
Among all the big sales regions, from South China to Northeast China,

218
00:13:58,530 --> 00:14:00,950
how many are B-end and how many are C-end customers?

219
00:14:00,950 --> 00:14:04,570
There are only B-end and there isn't a single C-end client.

220
00:14:04,570 --> 00:14:08,730
- It appears you know it well.
- However, this is exactly the biggest problem we're currently facing.

221
00:14:08,730 --> 00:14:12,810
What's the problem? Give up B-end clients and turn to C-end clients?

222
00:14:12,810 --> 00:14:16,060
Ruin the Great Wall ourselves and disable our own martial arts skills?

223
00:14:16,060 --> 00:14:20,130
Master, it's because our company has no C-end clients.

224
00:14:20,130 --> 00:14:24,650
Our entire company relies only on B-end customers to support our cash flow.

225
00:14:24,650 --> 00:14:26,690
Then if there is any trouble in the B-end customers,

226
00:14:26,690 --> 00:14:30,370
or if the competitor fights a price war, we'll become very passive.

227
00:14:30,370 --> 00:14:34,330
We can only choose to lower or even give up profit

228
00:14:34,330 --> 00:14:37,990
to maintain it, then... then is this an effective solution?

229
00:14:37,990 --> 00:14:42,280
No, it isn't! We can only choose between loss and bankruptcy, whichever is the lessor of the two evils.

230
00:14:42,280 --> 00:14:44,980
Master, this is a road that waits for death.

231
00:14:44,980 --> 00:14:46,930
It looks like you aren't waiting to die.

232
00:14:46,930 --> 00:14:49,080
You're looking for an early death.

233
00:14:51,430 --> 00:14:55,080
Master. Master, listen to me!

234
00:14:55,850 --> 00:14:58,290
For the past ten years, our work has been gearing towards B-end clients.

235
00:14:58,290 --> 00:15:01,620
However, it's a fact that we're almost reaching the end of this road.

236
00:15:01,620 --> 00:15:04,340
If we don't get ahead before the next industrial wave arrives

237
00:15:04,340 --> 00:15:05,930
and expand our business to C-end,

238
00:15:05,930 --> 00:15:09,850
I really worry if we'll even be qualified to take part in the next round.

239
00:15:09,850 --> 00:15:13,950
With what you said, I fear it isn't just Jieke that is waiting to die.

240
00:15:13,950 --> 00:15:17,650
You want to tell me that I'm waiting to die.

241
00:15:17,650 --> 00:15:19,920
Master,

242
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:22,400
no one stands taller than you in Jieke,

243
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:24,680
and no one sees farther than you do.

244
00:15:24,680 --> 00:15:28,950
If even I can see it, then you must've seen it long ago.

245
00:15:28,950 --> 00:15:31,690
However, I really don't understand.

246
00:15:31,690 --> 00:15:34,640
Why do you keep delaying on taking action?

247
00:15:35,590 --> 00:15:37,880
There is a hurtful phrase.

248
00:15:40,020 --> 00:15:43,630
Back then, I said it to someone else.

249
00:15:48,690 --> 00:15:51,030
I even pledged an oath

250
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:56,420
that I would never say it to anyone else in this lifetime.

251
00:16:00,080 --> 00:16:02,120
But today,

252
00:16:02,630 --> 00:16:04,340
I can't help but say it to you.

253
00:16:04,340 --> 00:16:06,250
What is it?

254
00:16:06,250 --> 00:16:09,380
In your entire life, you've only ever been able to be a tech person.

255
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:21,360
After you said this back then, he left.

256
00:16:21,360 --> 00:16:24,470
That was the last thing I said to him.

257
00:16:25,570 --> 00:16:28,060
I won't shirk from responsibility, and I didn't want to anger you.

258
00:16:28,060 --> 00:16:31,370
But Master, you're wrong.

259
00:16:32,260 --> 00:16:34,750
You're exactly like him.

260
00:16:35,920 --> 00:16:38,370
Consider that I'm blind then.

261
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:50,860
The established reality is already in front of us.

262
00:16:51,380 --> 00:16:53,550
I don't want to sit and wait for death.

263
00:16:53,550 --> 00:16:56,480
I also don't want to see Jieke, the company that I've fought alongside you these past ten years,

264
00:16:56,480 --> 00:17:00,520
and the Master whom I've followed for ten years to slowly fall into an abyss.

265
00:17:01,260 --> 00:17:03,870
I'll wait for my death, and you can seek your own death.

266
00:17:03,870 --> 00:17:07,380
Master, then you'll live a life that's worse than death.

267
00:17:07,380 --> 00:17:10,840
- Then what about you?
- Me?

268
00:17:10,840 --> 00:17:13,350
I'll go towards death in order to stay alive.

269
00:17:22,380 --> 00:17:25,080
